As a results of ongoing Demutualisation of The Nigerian Stock Exchange and restructure it to Nigerian Exchange Group Plc, The National Council of the Exchange is pleased to announce that the following Chief Executives will head its operating and non-operating companies till the completion of its ongoing demutualisation:  Advert These appointments are subject to the approval of the Securities and Exchange Commission. Under the demutualisation plan, a new non-operating holding company, the Nigerian Exchange Group plc (NGX Group) has been created. The Group will have three operating subsidiaries – Nigerian Exchange Limited (NGX), the operating exchange; NGX Regulation Limited (NGX REGCO), the independent regulatory arm; and NGX Real Estate Limited (NGX RELCO), the real estate company – forming the group. All the entities have been duly registered at the Corporate Affairs Commission (“CAC”).  End.